properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 21 at 2:31PM PST until January 22 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...SNOW WEDNESDAY...

.A warm front will bring snow to the Washington Cascades and
northern Blue mountains Wednesday. Snow levels will begin to rise
Wednesday night eventually changing precipitation to rain below
5000 feet.

* WHAT...Snow expected below 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of up to 5 inches around Cle Elum and Easton. Higher amounts
near the crest of 8 to 12 inches.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 10 PM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Precipitation will begin to change over to
rain Wednesday evening.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 10 PM PST WEDNESDAY BELOW 3000 FEET
